This is probably 4th August 1915, the anniversary of the outbreak of WWI.

According to the Times &quot;It will be a day of intercession and prayer, and of the dedication of the British people to the fulfillment of the vows of the Empire on the first day of the war.&quot;

The King and Queen attended a service in St Paul's at noon,  travelling privately and without state ceremonial.
